      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TACTICALLY PERFECT NZ (2) went straight to the paddock after kicking off her career with an impressive win at Charlton in December when she overcame a second row draw to cruise home by 12m. Likely to have developed further with maturity and she was readied with a trial placing. A good draw could see her make a winning return. COLOSIMO (3) continues to race well, putting together a string of top-four finishes since breaking his maiden from this barrier at Maryborough. Has come from the back row to miss by narrow margins in the last two outings. A better draw could see him atone. SHIFFRIN (1) is ticking along well having placed twice in her last three outings, both from second line draws. Should enjoy the favours from the inside barrier. HILTONS SPIRIT (5) has been good so far this time in, winning fresh at Kilmore and recording a 1.2m third from the back line last time at Melton. Go well again.",
